The Eagles are currently locked in action with Pep Guardiola’s men at the Etihad, in their latest Premier League outing. Palace of course headed into proceedings as heavy underdogs, with the capital outfit having managed just a solitary win from their last 7 in the English top-flight. Hosts City, on the other hand, are flying high on the back of 7-straight victories across all competitions. The Sky Blues were also boosted, meanwhile, by the result of the weekend’s marquee Premier League fixture, which saw Liverpool and Manchester United play out a 0-0 draw at Anfield earlier this evening. <img src="https://www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/GettyImages-1296887704.jpg" alt="Explanation provided for Wilfried Zaha’s absence from Crystal Palace squad vs Man City"/> LIVERPOOL, ENGLAND – JANUARY 17: Thiago of Liverpool challenges for the ball with Bruno Fernandes of Manchester United during the Premier League match between Liverpool and Manchester United at Anfield on January 17, 2021 in Liverpool, England. Sporting stadiums around England remain under strict restrictions due to the Coronavirus Pandemic as Government social distancing laws prohibit fans inside venues resulting in games being played behind closed doors. (Photo by Michael Regan/Getty Images) As such, ahead of kick-off in Manchester, Palace were no doubt aware that a testing 90 minutes lay in store. It therefore came as a major blow for the Eagles faithful when, just an hour prior to proceedings getting underway, it was revealed that the club’s star man would play no part versus City. Upon the visitors’ starting XI being unveiled, neither Wilfried Zaha or Cheikhou Kouyaté were anywhere to be seen: COME ON YOU PALACE#CPFC | #MCICRY — Crystal Palace F.C. (@CPFC) January 17, 2021 In turn, speaking during a pre-match interview at the Etihad, Roy Hodgson was inevitably drawn on the absence of the aforementioned pair. And the Palace boss went on to confirm: ‘Cheikhou’s got a family situation which meant that he wasn’t able to be with us on this occasion, and Wilf unfortunately picked up a knock, an injury in the game against Arsenal.’ Hodgson continued: ‘Every time Wilf doesn’t play it’s a miss, that’s been well-documented.’ ‘We’d loved to have had him here, we’d loved to have had Cheik [Kouyate] here as well but these things happen in a game of football.’ Roy Hodgson explains his team selection at Man City – with Wilfried Zaha missing out Watch live on Sky Sports PL pic.twitter.com/2JEAMsAL5z — Sky Sports Premier League (@SkySportsPL) January 17, 2021 Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.